    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note1",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 705,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 42,
      "text": "DHT22 (Temp/Humidity Sensor)\nMeasures ambient temperature and humidity. Digital output on 'out' pin.\nUsed to monitor environmental conditions in the watchdog system.",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 802,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "DHT22 (Temp/Humidity Sensor)\nMeasures ambient temperature and humidity. Digital output on 'out' pin.\nUsed to monitor environmental conditions in the watchdog system.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 110272005,
      "index": "b0w",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note2",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 755,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 42,
      "text": "SW-420 (Vibration Sensor)\nDetects vibration/motion via spring-based mechanism. DO pin goes LOW on vibration.\nUsed for tamper detection - alerts if enclosure is disturbed.",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 803,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "SW-420 (Vibration Sensor)\nDetects vibration/motion via spring-based mechanism. DO pin goes LOW on vibration.\nUsed for tamper detection - alerts if enclosure is disturbed.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1475473611,
      "index": "b0x",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note3",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 805,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 42,
      "text": "Active Buzzer\nGenerates audible tone when I/O pin is driven HIGH. Built-in oscillator.\nUsed for audible alarms and alerts (tamper, temperature warnings).",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 804,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Active Buzzer\nGenerates audible tone when I/O pin is driven HIGH. Built-in oscillator.\nUsed for audible alarms and alerts (tamper, temperature warnings).",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1291490661,
      "index": "b0y",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note4",
      "x": 480,
      "y": 705,
      "width": 430,
      "height": 42,
      "text": "RGB LED (Common Cathode)\nThree LEDs in one package sharing a common ground (pin 2, longest leg).\nUsed for visual status indication - different colors represent system states.",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 805,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "RGB LED (Common Cathode)\nThree LEDs in one package sharing a common ground (pin 2, longest leg).\nUsed for visual status indication - different colors represent system states.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 95395691,
      "index": "b0z",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note5",
      "x": 480,
      "y": 755,
      "width": 430,
      "height": 42,
      "text": "220\u03a9 Resistors (Current Limiting)\nLimit current through each LED to ~10mA at 3.3V: (3.3V - 2V) / 220\u03a9 \u2248 6mA.\nProtects LEDs from overcurrent damage and ensures consistent brightness.",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 806,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "220\u03a9 Resistors (Current Limiting)\nLimit current through each LED to ~10mA at 3.3V: (3.3V - 2V) / 220\u03a9 \u2248 6mA.\nProtects LEDs from overcurrent damage and ensures consistent brightness.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 640458949,
      "index": "b10",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note6",
      "x": 480,
      "y": 805,
      "width": 430,
      "height": 55,
      "text": "100nF Ceramic Capacitor (Decoupling/Bypass)\nFilters high-frequency noise from power supply. Placed between 3V3 and GND rails.\nStabilizes voltage during current spikes, prevents sensor glitches.\nCode: '104' = 10 \u00d7 10\u2074 pF = 100nF. Ceramic caps have no polarity.",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 807,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "100nF Ceramic Capacitor (Decoupling/Bypass)\nFilters high-frequency noise from power supply. Placed between 3V3 and GND rails.\nStabilizes voltage during current spikes, prevents sensor glitches.\nCode: '104' = 10 \u00d7 10\u2074 pF = 100nF. Ceramic caps have no polarity.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 419330571,
      "index": "b11",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note7",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 865,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 55,
      "text": "ESP32-S3-DevKitC-1-N32R8V (Microcontroller)\nDual-core Xtensa LX7 @ 240MHz with WiFi/BLE. 32MB Flash + 8MB PSRAM.\nBuilt-in RGB LED on GPIO48 (WS2812). Power via either USB port (5V in, 3.3V regulated).\nBOOT button (GPIO0): Hold during reset to enter bootloader mode.",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 808,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "ESP32-S3-DevKitC-1-N32R8V (Microcontroller)\nDual-core Xtensa LX7 @ 240MHz with WiFi/BLE. 32MB Flash + 8MB PSRAM.\nBuilt-in RGB LED on GPIO48 (WS2812). Power via either USB port (5V in, 3.3V regulated).\nBOOT button (GPIO0): Hold during reset to enter bootloader mode.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1472610341,
      "index": "b12",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note8",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 930,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 55,
      "text": "Native USB Port (labeled 'USB')\nDirect connection to ESP32-S3 USB OTG controller (GPIO19/20).\nSupports: USB CDC serial, JTAG debugging, DFU firmware upload.\nWSL2: /dev/ttyACM0. Limitation: Disconnects on device reset (re-enumeration).",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 809,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Native USB Port (labeled 'USB')\nDirect connection to ESP32-S3 USB OTG controller (GPIO19/20).\nSupports: USB CDC serial, JTAG debugging, DFU firmware upload.\nWSL2: /dev/ttyACM0. Limitation: Disconnects on device reset (re-enumeration).",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 517537963,
      "index": "b13",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note9",
      "x": 480,
      "y": 865,
      "width": 430,
      "height": 55,
      "text": "UART Port (labeled 'UART')\nUses Silicon Labs CP2102N USB-to-UART bridge chip. VID:PID 10c4:ea60.\nSupports: Serial @ 115200 baud (up to 3Mbps), auto-reset via RTS/DTR.\nWSL2: /dev/ttyUSB0. Advantage: Survives device resets (bridge stays powered).",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 810,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "UART Port (labeled 'UART')\nUses Silicon Labs CP2102N USB-to-UART bridge chip. VID:PID 10c4:ea60.\nSupports: Serial @ 115200 baud (up to 3Mbps), auto-reset via RTS/DTR.\nWSL2: /dev/ttyUSB0. Advantage: Survives device resets (bridge stays powered).",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 397734789,
      "index": "b14",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "note10",
      "x": 480,
      "y": 930,
      "width": 430,
      "height": 55,
      "text": "Which USB Port to Use?\n\u2022 Flashing firmware: Either works. UART is more reliable (no reconnect needed).\n\u2022 Serial monitor: UART preferred (survives resets, sees boot messages).\n\u2022 JTAG debugging: Native USB only (direct to ESP32-S3 debug interface).",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#555555",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 811,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Which USB Port to Use?\n\u2022 Flashing firmware: Either works. UART is more reliable (no reconnect needed).\n\u2022 Serial monitor: UART preferred (survives resets, sees boot messages).\n\u2022 JTAG debugging: Native USB only (direct to ESP32-S3 debug interface).",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 552186699,
      "index": "b15",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "updated": 1772349413555,
      "autoResize": true
    },
